    "content": "<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n    <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n    <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\n    <title>Multiset</title>\n    <style>\n        body {\n            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\n        }\n        .container {\n            width: 80%;\n            margin: 40px auto;\n            padding: 20px;\n            border: 1px solid #ccc;\n            border-radius: 10px;\n            box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);\n        }\n        .multiset {\n            padding: 20px;\n            border: 1px solid #ccc;\n            border-radius: 10px;\n            box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);\n        }\n        .multiset h2 {\n            margin-top: 0;\n        }\n    </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n    <div class=\"container\">\n        <h2>Multiset</h2>\n        <p>A multiset is a set in which each element is associated with a set of indices. It is used to represent data that has multiple values for each unique element.</p>\n        <div class=\"multiset\">\n            <h3>Example 1</h3>\n            <p>Let's consider a multiset with the following elements: {a: 2, b: 3, c: 1}</p>\n            <p>Count: {a: 2, b: 3, c: 1}</p>\n            <button id=\"add\">Add</button>\n            <button id=\"remove\">Remove</button>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"multiset\">\n            <h3>Example 2</h3>\n            <p>Let's consider a multiset with the following elements: {x: 2, y: 3, z: 1}</p>\n            <p>Count: {x: 2, y: 3, z: 1}</p>\n            <button id=\"add2\">Add</button>\n            <button id=\"remove2\">Remove</button>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <script>\n        let count = 0;\n        let elements = {};\n\n        document.getElementById('add').addEventListener('click', () => {\n            let element = document.getElementById('multiset').children[count].textContent;\n            if (element in elements) {\n                elements[element].count++;\n            } else {\n                elements[element] = {count: 1, value: element};\n            }\n            count++;\n            updateCount();\n        });\n\n        document.getElementById('remove').addEventListener('click', () => {\n            let element = document.getElementById('multiset').children[count - 1].textContent;\n            if (element in elements) {\n                delete elements[element];\n                count--;\n                updateCount();\n            }\n        });\n\n        function updateCount() {\n            let output = '';\n            for (let element in elements) {\n                output += `${element}: ${elements[element].count} `;\n            }\n            document.getElementById('multiset h2').textContent = output;\n        }\n    </script>\n</body>\n</html>"
